# APPENDIX B: THE DORMITORY CODE

All children housed in Order dormitories are subject to the following rules:

1. Lights-out is at the ninth bell. Silence is mandatory after lights-out.
2. Wake-up is at the sixth bell. All children will be dressed and standing at the foot of their cots by the sixth bell's end.
3. Personal effects are limited to the contents of the assigned footlocker. No items from outside the Cradle are permitted.
4. Contact between children of different Gates is limited to supervised training exercises and designated social hours. Unauthorized contact will result in Silk Isolation.
5. Physical contact between children is permitted only in the context of supervised training. Embracing, hand-holding, and other expressions of physical intimacy are discouraged and will be noted.
6. Children will address Handlers as "Handler," Instructors as "Instructor," and Savants as "Witness." No other forms of address are permitted.
7. Children will not discuss escape, resistance, or the outside world. Such discussions will be reported and investigated.
8. Children will not share personal histories. The past is irrelevant. Only the training matters.
9. Violations of the Dormitory Code will be met with corrective discipline as described in Section 4.5.

