# APPENDIX E: A NOTE ON THE WORD "MERCY"

The realms use the word "mercy" loosely. They mean kindness without cost, compassion without consequence. The Order does not traffic in such mercies. Our mercy is harder and more honest.

Our mercy is the silk that binds without bruising. Our mercy is the Handler's clean hands. Our mercy is the Instructor's relentless "Again," which shapes a child into something that can survive. Our mercy is the Savant's cold reading, which sees the child truly and does not flinch. Our mercy is Permanent Sedation for the child who would otherwise suffer a lifetime of fear and pain and eventual violent death at the hands of a predatory mage.

We do not claim to be kind. We claim to be necessary. The distinction is the difference between sentiment and salvation.

